{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0faed87b-fc24-42c4-9c65-bb9098256f1d","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 **dropped support for `net6.0` and `net7.0`**. The supported TFMs are:\n\n- **`net8.0`+** (for .NET)\n- **`net462`+** (for .NET Framework)\n\nYour project currently targets `net6.0` (which is also end-of-life since Nov 2024), so you'd need to **retarget to at least `net8.0`** before upgrading to MSTest v4.\n\nBeyond the TFM issue, your test code is simple and wouldn't hit any of the MSTest v4 API breaking changes. But the framework simply won't load on `net6.0`.\n\nWould you like me to upgrade both the TFM and MSTest version for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a6cbb2b6-88b4-42d2-881f-d6ad8f7bff15","outputTokens":189},"id":"d44f4ad4-e2e7-4e8f-b069-49c007d407ca","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:08.805Z","parentId":"7d2afc0a-af56-4619-aa0e-242345a906c5"}
